subject: Basketball
College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Rhode Island made it into the Associated Press men’s college basketball poll for the first time in nine years, entering at No. 25 after the program’s best start since the 1991-92 season. The Rams (11-1) were last ranked briefly in November 1998.For the fourth consecutive week, North Carolina, Memphis and Kansas were the top three teams in the rankings. Losses last week by No. 4 Texas, No. 5 Georgetown and No. 6 Duke moved Washington State (11-0) up three spots to No. 4, the highest ranking in team history.
